    <title>G</title>

    <glossentry id="gloss_groupware">
      <glossterm>Groupware</glossterm>
      <glossdef>
        <para>Generic term used to describe client/server applications used to provide email calendar (and other) services.  Groupware consists of a server and client.  Examples include Microsoft Exchange (server) and Outlook (client) and IBM Lotus Domino (server) and Notes (client).  Since the communication between client and server for groupware applications is propriatary to the groupware vendor, such communication often cannot be scanned.</para>
      </glossdef>            
    </glossentry>
    
  </glossdiv>

