      <glossterm>Simple Mail Transfer Protocol</glossterm>
      <acronym>SMTP</acronym>
      <glossdef>
        <para>Internet protocol used to transmit (send) email.  SMTP is the defacto way to send email between organizations.  Within a given organization, SMTP may or may not be used to send mails from user desktops to the organization's mail server.</para>
